  "prompt": "I have heard Reliance JIO locks a mobile phone and the same cannot be used for any other network. Is it true?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, Reliance JIO does offer certain mobile phones that are locked to their network, meaning they can only be used with a JIO SIM card and cannot be used with SIM cards from other networks. This practice is common among various telecom providers globally to ensure customer retention and to offer subsidized or lower-cost phones.\n\nHowever, not all JIO phones are network-locked, and you can find JIO-compatible phones that are unlocked and can be used with other carriers. If you are considering purchasing a phone from JIO, it's advisable to check whether the particular model is network-locked or not, either through official JIO sources or the phone's documentation.",
